AB  - The development of the dairy farming is important for environmental aspects, as well as social and economic development of the countryside in Sweden. When aiming at a sustainable dairy production it is crucial to include these issues, but animal health and welfare should also be considered. The overall aim of this study was to describe future scenarios for dairy farm production in Sweden, and to analyse sustainability of theses scenarios, using a method previously developed. Based on the construction of goal visions two scenarios for future dairy farms were constructed; Specialised Dairy Farming (SDF) with high production intensity and Mixed Dairy Farming (MDF) with increased crop rotations and large share of pasture. Based on the qualitative descriptions and the design of buildings, the farming systems were quantified. When quantification was performed the scenarios were evaluated concerning economics, environmental effects and animal welfare, including health. Cost of production was in scenario SDF 3.02 SEK/kg milk, in MDF 4.34 SEK/kg milk, and in the present Swedish dairy production 2.87 SEK/kg milk. Life Cycle Assessment included analyses of eutrophication, global warming potential, acidification and usage of pesticides. The contribution to eutrophication per litre milk was lower for scenario SDF, but MDF contributed less to eutrophication per land area used. Comparing the scenarios, MDF had more positive impact on the environment than SDF, based on our analysis. Cows in SDF were found to have an increased risk of lameness, mastitis, ketosis and abomasal displacement compared to cows in the MDF scenario. No scenario was superior in all aspects and the goal for developing Sustainable dairy farm production must be guided by analysis of values. However, the mainly positive environmental results for scenario MDF must be considered as rather strong, since the assumed milk yield is rather low. No system is the sole solution and choices has to be made, and studies of this kind make it possible to survey which choices that can be made and what the consequences are.
