AB  - This paper discusses the value creation process of sustainable public transport and tries to develop the debate concerning the question value for whom in the context of public transport. The empirical foundations are collected in two case studies of Swedish Public Transportation Authorities (PTA) and a public transport hydrogen bus project of Hamburg in Germany. Our arguments follow the service centred logic (Vargo and Lusch, 2004) which is a dynamic and flexible approach. Instead of talking about the dichotomy of common good and customer value we talk about creating stakeholder value from a stakeholder view which also includes the business ethic question, value for whom? Triple Bottom Line (TBL) issues (Environment, Society, and Economy) (Elkington, 1998) is better understood having a more holistic, open and integrative lens. We will see transportation and the environment, economy, society and safety as part of the value creating processes for creating a sustainable public transport.
